    {
      "type": "FeatureTrack",
      "trackId": "hg38-pbsv",
      "name": "Long-read Variants - CoLoRSdb structural variants",
      "assemblyNames": [
        "hg38"
      ],
      "description": "CoLoRSdb long-read structural variants",
      "category": [
        "Variation and Repeats"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "ucsc": {
          "bigDataUrl": "/gbdb/hg38/colorsDb/colorsDb.v1.2.0.sv.bb",
          "filter.AC": "0",
          "filter.svLen": "0",
          "filterByRange.AC": "on",
          "filterByRange.svLen": "on",
          "filterLabel.AC": "Alt allele count (AC)",
          "filterLabel.svLen": "SV length (bp)",
          "filterLabel.svType": "Type",
          "filterLimits.AC": "0:3000",
          "filterLimits.svLen": "0:12000",
          "filterType.svType": "multiple",
          "filterValues.svType": "INS,DEL,INV",
          "html": "<h2>Description</h2>\n<p>\n  The Consortium of Long Read Sequencing (CoLoRSdb) catalogs both small genetic variants\n  (single nucleotide polymorphisms and short insertions and deletions) and structural\n  variants (insertions, deletions, and inversions) discovered from long-read whole genome\n  sequencing. Long reads improve sensitivity and breakpoint resolution compared to\n  short-read data, especially for repeats and complex loci.\n</p>\n<p>\n  For more information, see the CoLoRSdb website:\n  <a href=\"https://colorsdb.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">https://colorsdb.org/</a>\n</p>\n\n<h2>Display Conventions and Configuration</h2>\n\n<h4>Small variants (DeepVariant + GLnexus)</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    DeepVariant + GLnexus tracks are shown using the <a href=\"/goldenPath/help/hgVcfTrackHelp.html\"\n    target=\"_blank\">VCF display format</a>.</li>\n  <li>\n    In <em>dense</em> mode, each variant appears as a single pixel.</li>\n  <li>\n    In <em>pack</em> or <em>full</em> modes, clicking a variant reveals the reference and\n    alternate alleles (REF/ALT), the quality score (QUAL), the filter status (FILTER), and fields\n    from the INFO column.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>Structural variants (pbsv + Jasmine)</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    Structural variants are rendered as intervals with spans and block structures when applicable.\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <b>Coloring</b> for each item is based on the variant type:\n    <ul>\n      <li><span style=\"display:inline-block;width:12px;height:12px;background:#ff0000;border:1px solid #000;vertical-align:middle;margin-right:6px;\"></span> Deletion (DEL) = red</li>\n      <li><span style=\"display:inline-block;width:12px;height:12px;background:#0000ff;border:1px solid #000;vertical-align:middle;margin-right:6px;\"></span> Insertion (INS) = blue</li>\n      <li><span style=\"display:inline-block;width:12px;height:12px;background:#800080;border:1px solid #000;vertical-align:middle;margin-right:6px;\"></span> Inversion (INV) = purple</li>\n    </ul>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    Mouseover an item reveals the genomic position, structural variant type,\n    variant length, allele frequency, alternative allele count, number of samples, total allele\n    number, Hardy-Weinburg equilibrium (HWE) p-value, and excess heterozygosity (ExcHet) p-value.\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Methods</h2>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Small variants:</strong> Per-sample variant calling was performed with DeepVariant,\n      followed by joint genotyping across the cohort using GLnexus.</li>\n  <li><strong>Structural variants:</strong> Called from long-read sequencing data using pbsv and\n      merged using Jasmine across individuals. The VCF file was converted to a bigBed file for\n      efficient display.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Data Access</h2>\n<p>\nThe CoLoRSdb track can be explored interactively using the\n<a href=\"https://genome.ucsc.edu/goldenPath/help/api.html\" target=\"_blank\">REST API</a>, the\n<a href=\"https://genome.ucsc.edu/cgi-bin/hgTables\" target=\"_blank\">Table Browser</a>, or the\n<a href=\"https://genome.ucsc.edu/cgi-bin/hgIntegrator\" target=\"_blank\">Data Integrator</a>. \nThe VCF and bigBed files are available from our \n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://hgdownload.soe.ucsc.edu/gbdb/hg38/colorsDb/\">\ndownloads directory</a>.\nThe original VCF files are part of the v1.2.0 dataset, and documentation is available on Zenodo:\n<a href=\"https://zenodo.org/records/14814308\"\ntarget=\"_blank\">https://zenodo.org/records/14814308</a>\n</p>\n\n<h2>Credits</h2>\n<p>\nThanks to Mike Schatz, Evan Eichler, and all <a href=\"https://colorsdb.org/membership\"\ntarget=\"_blank\">CoLoRSdb investigators</a> for generating and making the data publicly available.\n</p>\n\n<h2>References</h2>\n\n<p>\nEisfeldt J, Ameur A, Lenner F, Ten Berk de Boer E, Ek M, Wincent J, Vaz R, Ottosson J, Jonson T,\nIvarsson S <em>et al</em>.\n<a href=\"http://genome.cshlp.org/lookup/pmidlookup?view=long&amp;pmid=39472022\" target=\"_blank\">\nA national long-read sequencing study on chromosomal rearrangements uncovers hidden\ncomplexities</a>.\n<em>Genome Res</em>. 2024 Nov 20;34(11):1774-1784.\nDOI: <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1101/gr.279510.124\" target=\"_blank\">10.1101/gr.279510.124</a>;\nPMID: <a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/39472022\" target=\"_blank\">39472022</a>; PMC: <a\nhref=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC11610602/\" target=\"_blank\">PMC11610602</a>\n</p>\n<p>\nKirsche M, Prabhu G, Sherman R, Ni B, Battle A, Aganezov S, Schatz MC.\n<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1038/s41592-022-01753-3\" target=\"_blank\">\nJasmine and Iris: population-scale structural variant comparison and analysis</a>.\n<em>Nat Methods</em>. 2023 Mar;20(3):408-417.\nDOI: <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1038/s41592-022-01753-3\"\ntarget=\"_blank\">10.1038/s41592-022-01753-3</a>; PMID: <a\nhref=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/36658279\" target=\"_blank\">36658279</a>; PMC: <a\nhref=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC10006329/\" target=\"_blank\">PMC10006329</a>\n</p>\n<p>\nLake, J. A., &amp; Consortium of Long Read Sequencing (CoLoRS).\n<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.14814308\" target=\"_blank\">Consortium of Long Read\nSequencing Database (CoLoRSdb) (v1.2.0) [Data set]</a> <em>Zendo</em>. 2025 Feb 5.\n<a href=https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.14814308 target=\"_blank\">10.5281/zenodo.14814308</a>\n</p>\n<p>\nPoplin R, Chang PC, Alexander D, Schwartz S, Colthurst T, Ku A, Newburger D, Dijamco J, Nguyen N,\nAfshar PT <em>et al</em>.\n<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1038/nbt.4235\" target=\"_blank\">\nA universal SNP and small-indel variant caller using deep neural networks</a>.\n<em>Nat Biotechnol</em>. 2018 Nov;36(10):983-987.\nDOI: <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1038/nbt.4235\" target=\"_blank\">10.1038/nbt.4235</a>; PMID: <a\nhref=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/30247488\" target=\"_blank\">30247488</a>\n</p>\n<p>\nYun T, Li H, Chang PC, Lin MF, Carroll A, McLean CY.\n<a href=\"https://academic.oup.com/bioinformatics/article-lookup/doi/10.1093/bioinformatics/btaa1081\"\ntarget=\"_blank\">\nAccurate, scalable cohort variant calls using DeepVariant and GLnexus</a>.\n<em>Bioinformatics</em>. 2021 Apr 5;36(24):5582-5589.\nDOI: <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1093/bioinformatics/btaa1081\"\ntarget=\"_blank\">10.1093/bioinformatics/btaa1081</a>; PMID: <a\nhref=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/33399819\" target=\"_blank\">33399819</a>; PMC: <a\nhref=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8023681/\" target=\"_blank\">PMC8023681</a>\n</p>\n",
          "itemRgb": "on",
          "longLabel": "CoLoRSdb long-read structural variants",
          "mouseOver": "<b>Position</b>: $chrom:${chromStart}-${chromEnd}<br> <b>SV type</b>: ${svType}<br> <b>Length</b>: ${svLen} bp<br> <b>Allele Frequency</b>: ${af}<br> <b>Alt allele count</b>: ${AC} (Hom: ${AC_Hom}, Het: ${AC_Het}, Hemi: ${AC_Hemi})<br> <b>Number of samples</b>: ${NS} <br> <b>Total allele number</b>: ${AN}<br> <b>HWE p-value</b>: ${HWE}<br> <b>ExcHet</b>: ${ExcHet}",
          "parent": "longReadVariants",
          "searchIndex": "name,svType",
          "shortLabel": "CoLoRSdb structural variants",
          "track": "pbsv",
          "type": "bigBed 9 +",
          "visibility": "pack"
        }
      },
